    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(19-21) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then came to him his mother and his brethren.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—See Notes on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 12:46-50",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 3:31-35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". There cannot be any doubt that we have in those passages a report of the same incident; but it may be noted that St. Luke places it after the teaching by parables, and the other two Gospels before. In this instance the evidence preponderates in favour of the latter sequence of events.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For the press.—Better, by reason of the multitude.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "For the press.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Better, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "by reason of the multitude.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
